rmative and discursive expressions of ethnicity. Confrontational encounters stimulated by economic and political rivalry, as well as socially integrative processes, transformed collective self-understanding in Cameroon in conjunction with recent global discourses on human, minority, and indigenous rights. The book provides a vital contribution to the study of ethnicity, conflict, and social change in the anthropology of Africa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aEthnic conflictxCameroon. 0aEthnic conflictzCameroon. 0aEthnic relationsxPolitical aspects. 0aEthnicityxCameroon. 0aEthnicityzCameroon. 70(DE-588)4023698-50(DE-627)1063021670(DE-576)208951008aHausa2gnd 70(DE-588)4026482-80(DE-627)1062881990(DE-576)208966544aIdentität2gnd 70(DE-588)4034026-00(DE-627)1062548630(DE-576)209004657aLändlicher Raum2gnd 70(DE-588)4063790-60(DE-627)1041066030(DE-576)209150475aVolk2gnd 70(DE-588)4138634-60(DE-627)1056412270(DE-576)20968772XaStammgEthnologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4164958-80(DE-627)1054434840(DE-576)20989217XaKonfliktregelung2gnd 70(DE-588)4169999-30(DE-627)1043929750(DE-576)209926821aMinderheitenfrage2gnd 70(DE-588)4176973-90(DE-627)1053521600(DE-576)209974257aEthnische Beziehungen2gnd 70(DE-588)4225814-50(DE-627)1049763490(DE-576)210309229aBororogFulbe2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782387299?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782387299423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782387299/original  a978-3-11-099823-8  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA